Thanks for pointing this out. This is a neat edge-case. When you setup the filter, the bufferevent control callback becomes `be_filter_ctrl`, which without filtering is `be_socket_ctrl`. The difference is: be_socket_ctrl assigns all the proper read and write events on the fd. `be_filter_ctrl` does nothing.

@nmathewson does the referenced pull request make sense?

May want to do the same for GET_FD too.

@LudwigOrtmann you can try out that patch https://github.com/ellzey/Libevent/commit/c2aa7dcb70635844134b54df4ccdf4d547a0b2b4 but you need to also add this to your in/out filter functions to avoid an infinite loop.

``` C
evbuffer_remove_buffer(src, dst, evbuffer_get_length(src));
```
